ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp.DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt: DELIVERED EIGHT KITCHEN KITS, PLUS EXTRA KITCHEN SUPPLIES AND 4 BEDDING/BATH KITS TO NORTHWEST PILOT PROJECT, MARCH 14. DELIVERED 4 ADDITIONAL KITS IN DECEMBER. WORKED WITH COLUMBIA HOME ECONOMISTS IN HOME AND COMMUNITY TO SEW 56 PILLOW CASES, 26 HOT PADS AND SCRUBBERS NEEDED BY NORTHWEST PILOT PROJECT FOR BEDDING AND KITCHEN KITS TO GIVE TO VERY LOW-INCOME OLDER ADULTS WHEN HOUSING IS FOUND. MEMBERS SEWED THE PILLOW CASES AND HOT PADS AT THEIR HOMES AND DELIVERED THEM TO ME. CONTRIBUTED TIME AND SUPPLIES TO HELP FIVE OLDER ADULTS WHO NEEDED TRANSPORTATION, AND TWO WITH DOWNSIZING, MOVING, ETC. ALSO CLEARED AND CLEANED THE APARTMENT OF A 90-YEAR-OLD GENTLEMAN AT TOUCHMARK IN VANCOUVER, FOLLOWING HIS DEATH.

CONSULTED WITH INDIVIDUALS AND FAMILIES ABOUT AGING-RELATED CONCERNS INVOLVING FAMILY MEMBERS; HELD FAMILY MEETINGS WITH FAMILIES FACED WITH CONCERNS AND DECISIONS ABOUT AN AGING FAMILY MEMBER; AND WORKED WITH ELDERS AROUND AGING-RELATED CONCERNS AND/OR DECISIONS. CONSULTED WITH PROFESSIONALS AND PRACTITIONERS VIA TELEPHONE, EMAIL AND IN-PERSON ABOUT AGING-RELATED ISSUES, FAMILY AND CAREGIVING CONCERNS, AND RESOURCES/TRAINING MATERIALS. THIS INCLUDED REVIEWING MATERIALS FOR POWERFUL TOOLS FOR CAREGIVERS PROGRAM FOR IOWA STATE UNIVERSITY EXTENSION SERVICE. INVOLVED IN THE ALZHEIMER'S DISEASE AWARENESS FOR CHILDREN STORYBOOK PROGRAM WITH MONTANA STATE UNIVERSITY EXTENSION SERVICE, BOZEMAN. SERVED AS A CONSULTANT TO THE PROJECT AND RESEARCH PROGRAM: BE EPIC: PERSON-CENTERED COMMUNICATION WITH HOME CARE CLIENTS WITH DEMENTIA, HEALTH SCIENCES, WESTERN UNIVERSITY, ONTARIO, CANADA (MARIE SAVUNDRANAGAM),

GAVE MULTIPLE PRESENTATIONS AND AND INTERVIEWS, INCLUDING THE FOLLOWING: PREPARE TO CARE TRAINING FOR SPEAKERS OF THE AARP SPEAKER'S BUREAU, FEBRUARY 28 (VIRTUAL) A CAREGIVING CONVERSATION, OREGON AARP, MARCH 10 (VIRTUAL; PRESENTATION WAS A PART OF A MOVIE SCREENING OF FRONT PORCHES) A WOMAN OF INFLUENCE, OREGON AARP, MARCH 10 (VIRTUAL, RECORDED) UNDERSTANDING ALZHEIMER'S: IMPACT ON MEMORY AND BEHAVIOR, MONTANA STATE UNIVERSITY, MAY 21, 2022 (VIRTUAL) CAREGIVER FATIGUE, MARY'S WOODS RETIREMENT CENTER, LAKE OSWEGO, AUGUST 26. BRAIN HEALTH & DEMENTIA, NORTHWEST PLACE, PORTLAND, SEPTEMBER 26. FINDING THE RIGHT CONSULTED WITH OPB ABOUT AN OPB PROGRAM, THINK OUT LOUD, AND I WAS ON STANDBY" FOR THE TAPING OF THE PROGRAM, WHICH WAS FOCUSED ON INDIVIDUALS CURRENTLY IN A CAREGIVING ROLE TO A FAMILY MEMBER, MAY 25. WAS INTERVIEWED BY MAC MCLEAN FOR AN ARTICLE ON FAMILY CAREGIVING AND AARP'S ROLE AS A RESOURCE, AUGUST 17. ARTICLE, "FOR CAREGIVERS, STRESS-AND HELP", AARP BULLETIN, NOV. 2022, P. 44. WAS INTERVIEWED BY ERIC TEGETHOFF WITH THE OREGON NEWS SERVICE, NOVEMBER 21. "GIVING THANKS IN OR DURING FAMILY CAREGIVERS MONTH" NOVEMBER 22.
